        {
            "id": "https://a-slide.github.io/about.html",
            "url": "https://a-slide.github.io/about.html",
            "title": "About me",
            "summary": "In briefI&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<h2 class=\"md-end-block md-heading md-focus\" ><span class=\"md-expand\">In brief</span></h2>\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"md-line md-end-block\" ><span class=\"\">I am a </span><span class=\"\"><strong>computational biologist</strong></span> currently working as a senior postdoc at the EMBL-EBI in Ewan Birney's Team. I have a <span class=\"\"><strong>dual background in molecular biology and bioinformatics</strong></span><span class=\"\">. My PhD was at the bench in </span><span class=\"\"><strong>virology</strong></span> and <span class=\"\"><strong>epigenetics</strong></span> at the INSERM 1089 (University of Nantes, France). I had the opportunity to setup my own team in my PhD lab as a junior team leader and to obtain a master's degree in bioinformatics. I then moved to the EMBL-EBI to expend my skills in data analysis and software development. I have been working on a broad range of topics including <span class=\"\"><strong>RNA modifications in cancer</strong></span> and more recently medaka fish <span class=\"\"><strong>functional genomics</strong></span>.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"md-line md-end-block\" >Have a look at my ORCID, google scholar and impact stories profile to know more about my academic track record</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8772-6776\"><img loading=\"lazy\" style=\"padding: 5px;\" src=\"https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/orcid.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" srcset=\"https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/orcid-xs.png 300w ,https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/orcid-sm.png 480w ,https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/orcid-md.png 749w ,https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/orcid-xl.png 1200w\"  alt=\"\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\">ORCID Profile</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=SA5LcXgAAAAJ\"><img loading=\"lazy\" style=\"padding: 5px;\" src=\"https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/scholar.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" srcset=\"https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/scholar-xs.png 300w ,https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/scholar-sm.png 480w ,https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/scholar-md.png 749w ,https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/scholar-xl.png 1200w\"  alt=\"\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\">Google Scholar Profile</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://profiles.impactstory.org/u/0000-0001-8772-6776\"><img loading=\"lazy\" style=\"padding: 5px;\" src=\"https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/impact_story.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" srcset=\"https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/impact_story-xs.png 300w ,https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/impact_story-sm.png 480w ,https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/impact_story-md.png 749w ,https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/responsive/impact_story-xl.png 1200w\"  alt=\"\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\">Impact Story Profile</a></p>\n<h2>My personal life</h2>\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"md-line md-end-block\" >I am the dad of a bright and hyperactive 2 years old boy, meaning that most of my personal life is spent being a clown / life coach / cook / tower builder... Which I enjoy obviously. I am climbing/bouldering on a regular basis but nowhere as much as in secondary school, where I met my wonderful partner. Cycling is the other big drive of my life. As far as I can remember I have always been into cycling, one way or another. </span><span class=\"md-line md-end-block\" ><span class=\"\">Crazy as it might seems, our little family is planning a 1 year long cycling journey across Europe and Asia... Yes it is for real.</span></span></p>",
            "image": "https://a-slide.github.io/media/posts/2/books.jpg",
            "author": {
